<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>jasmine.exe</title>
<style>
  body {
    background-color: #FFFACD; /* LemonChiffon */
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #333;
    font-size: 1.5em;
  }

  #image-container {
    margin: 20px auto;
    max-width: 400px;
  }

  img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
  }

  button {
    background-color: #F08080; /* LightCoral */
    color: white;
    border: none;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    font-size: 1em;
    font-weight: bold;
    border-radius: 5px;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-top: 15px;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  button:hover {
    background-color: #CD5C5C; /* Darker hover */
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>These are my fav pics on my phone atm</h1>

<div id="image-container">
  <img id="pic" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Favorite Pic">
</div>

<button id="nextBtn">Next</button>

<button id="exitBtn">Exit</button>
<script>
  document.getElementById('exitBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (confirm("oh ok that's cool - see ya later I guess")) {
      // You can't close the tab unless it was script-opened, so just navigate away:
      window.location.href = 'about:blank';
    }
  });
</script>

<script>
  const images = [
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
  ];

  let currentIndex = 0;
  const pic = document.getElementById("pic");
  const btn = document.getElementById("nextBtn");

  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    currentIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % images.length;
    pic.src = images[currentIndex];
  });
</script>

</body>
</html>
